By Vivian Ibobo Ikeja – An Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court on Monday remanded three men in kirikiri Prison over alleged armed robbery. The defendants, Yusuf Tajudeen, 21; Salisu Kabiri, 20; and Abubakar Sani, 22; are being tried for conspiracy and armed robbery. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs M.I. Dan-Oni, ordered that the defendants should be kept in the Kirikiri Prisons, Lagos, pending advice from the state Directorate of Public Prosecutions (DPP). She directed that the case file should be sent to the DPP. Thus, the court did not take the defendants’ plea. Dan-Oni adjourned the case until Aug. 8, for mention. Earlier, the Prosecutor, Insp. Victor Eruada, told the court that the men committed the offences with others still at large on June 9, at 11:30p.m. at PPL Bus Stop, Ojo in Lagos. Eruada said that the suspects armed themself with cutlasses and kitchen knife, attacked one Miss Zuwaira Nasiru and robbed her of a Tecno cell phone worth N13,000 and an itel cell phone valued at N25,000. He said that the defendants also robbed one Mr Sumaila Abu of a Samsung cell phone worth N12,000 and a cash of N10,000 According to the prosecutor, the offences contravene Sections 411 and 297 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015.